        <![CDATA[<p>Most everyone in the United States swears, but <a href="https://stronglang.wordpress.com/2015/07/28/mapping-the-united-swears-of-america/">the specific words used vary by region</a>. For example, "fuck" is popular in California but not so much in Oklahoma, which is the "crap" epicenter of America. "Motherfucker" is unusually popular in Maine, as is "shit" in the Southeast, "douche" in Iowa, and "fuckboy" in Jersey.</p>

